<title type="html"><![CDATA[The Reverence Imam Maalik Had For Narrating Hadeeth]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="https://forum.salafiri.com/viewtopic.php?t=1362&amp;p=1446#p1446"><![CDATA[
<strong><span style="font-size: 200%; line-height: normal">The Reverence Imam Maalik Had For Narrating Hadeeth</span></strong><br /><br />Abdullah bin Mubarak said, &quot;I was with Maalik and he was narrating to us a hadeeth of the messenger of Allah, salla Allahu alayhe wa sallam, (while doing so) he was bit by a scorpion 16 times!<br /><br />Maalik (grimaced) and he began to turn yellow, yet he continued to convey the hadeeth of the messenger of Allah, salla Allahu alayhe wa sallam.<br /><br />Once the gathering had come to an end and the people began to disperse, I said 'Oh Abu Abdullah, I saw you acting strange (after you were bit by the scorpion)?' and he (Maalik) said 'Yes, I had to remain patient (after being bit by the scorpion) out of respect for the hadeeth that I was narrating from the messenger of Allah salla Allahu alayhe wa sallam'.&quot;<br /><br /><em>Ad-Debaj Al-Mudhab<br />Ibn Farhun (d.799h)</em><br /><br />Al-Thamaraat Admin.<br />Umm Al-Quraa University<br />Makkah Al-Mukarramah, Kingdom of Saudi Arabia<br /><br /><!-- w --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.althamaraat.com">www.althamaraat.com</a><!-- w --><p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="https://forum.salafiri.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=56">Shehzad Sattar</a> â€” Sat Mar 25, 2017 3:52 pm</p><hr />
